itis pigmentosa.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033338,0.054153,0.068998,0.084851,0.085028,0.093799,0.10353,0.1002,0.09571,0.089951,0.097371,0.093077],"unified_progress":[0.014672,0.030734,0.041813,0.052983,0.058892,0.076194,0.079399,0.095516,0.10466,0.11068,0.14558,0.18888]},{"section":9,"text":"Could be \"Retinitis pigmentosa\" or \"RP\".","dimension":2,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033206,0.057218,0.070495,0.081383,0.086374,0.094347,0.10119,0.11019,0.10724,0.10051,0.092275,0.065576],"unified_progress":[0.012269,0.027104,0.036134,0.045275,0.051875,0.064937,0.070263,0.08848,0.1018,0.11459,0.15673,0.23054]},{"section":10,"text":"So answer: Retinitis pigmentosa.assistantfinal The patient is a young adult with classic night blindness (nyctalopia) and tunnel vision.","dimension":0,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.020408,0.030712,0.036095,0.043563,0.049348,0.069994,0.084801,0.098915,0.13311,0.16169,0.16094,0.11042],"unified_progress":[0.0161,0.027242,0.037941,0.048183,0.061485,0.081093,0.087,0.1017,0.11967,0.13484,0.14747,0.13727]},{"section":11,"text":"The intra\u2011ocular pressure is normal and the anterior segment is unremarkable, ruling out glaucoma or anterior segment disease.","dimension":15,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029193,0.041515,0.046762,0.04992,0.056342,0.066122,0.068545,0.081823,0.10412,0.14342,0.16292,0.14932],"unified_progress":[0.016496,0.032943,0.044579,0.053643,0.064721,0.077104,0.085862,0.10224,0.11311,0.12739,0.14055,0.14137]},{"section":12,"text":"Fundoscopic findings of arteriolar attenuation, a pale optic disc, and bone\u2011spicule pigmentation in the mid\u2011peripheral retina are characteristic of a hereditary retinal dystrophy.","dimension":9,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027971,0.040708,0.046631,0.050777,0.053262,0.059197,0.060882,0.072826,0.091613,0.13616,0.18808,0.17188],"unified_progress":[0.015679,0.034599,0.046528,